ROCKY MOUNTAIN SPOTTED FEVER - USA: BACKGROUND
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Tue, 12 Aug 2003 13:32:36 +0300
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: GIDEON (Global Infectious Disease and Epidemiology Network)


Some data on fatal Rocky Mountain spotted fever in the United States: 207
fatal cases were reported during 1961 to 1970. Various sources reported 224
and 304 fatal cases during 1983 to 1998. The true number is estimated at 612.
Year / fatal cases reported
1982 / 40
1983 / 35
1984 / 34
1985 / 22
1986 / 19
1987 / 21
1988 / 20
1989 / 10
1990 / 20
1991 / 13
1991 / 13
1992 / 13
1993 / 5
1994 / 9
1995 / 8
1996 / 6
1997 / 12
1998 / 3
--
Dr Steve Berger
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
